The Atlanta Hawks upset the Milwaukee Bucks 116-113 in Game 1 of the Eastern Conference after Trae Young dropped an epic 48 points and 11 rebounds for the Hawks on Wednesday. In the Western Conference, the Phoenix Suns won both games at home, leading 2-0 over the Los Angeles Clippers. Devin Booker was behind the Suns' first win with a 40-plus point triple-double while Deandre Ayton added the second win with a 0.9-second alley-oop dunk for the team. Host: Li Xiang Guest: Matthew Watson Cover designer: Feng Yuan Chief editor: Chen Ran Supervisor: Zhang Shilei